<br>
Not everyone has the capacity to be a doctor.  In order to get those few that can do it to go into the field, they are paid at a very high rate.  <br>
<br>
Few people love being a lawyer.  It is hard work and not nearly as glamorous as portrayed on LA Law.  If it did not have the potential to pay very well I would not be doing it.  It's all about finding someone qualified and getting them to do the job.  <br>
<br>
Teachers strike all the time.  Johnny is not going to be a derranged human being for the rest of his life if his teacher strikes for a year.  The problem is that someone else WILL do the job for that rate.  That is not a failure of capitalism.  That is a triumph.  The services are provided without unnecessary expenditures of tax dollars.  If the job has five people lining up to do it at $20k per year, why should they pay $30k per year?<br>
<br>
Socialism is BAAAAAD!<br>
<br>
