I know a LOT of lawyers, seeing as my father is one.  The majority of them LOVE their jobs.  I have a friend who got a summer job as essentially an errand-runner at a law firm.  The next summer, she was hired for paralegal-style work.  She majored in European History, and is currently working as a paralegal, saving money for law school.  Why?  Because she loves it.  No one _has_ to be a lawyer...if they hate it so much, they could always be a gas station attendant.  *shrug*  It bet it's less demanding.<br>
As for my education, it's like I said.  _I_ won't consider myself worthy of a position as a full-time teacher until I have that education.  I hate school; I want to make sure I can do what I set out to do.  I want to keep other children from hating school if I can.  Hopefully, the more I know, the better a job of that I can do!  As I said when debunking the class-envy argument, I have wealthy parents who also think I should have this schooling.  3 years is not much to sacrifice to do a good job at something I love.<br>
<br>
